    rationale: "Informed consent includes the right to informed refusal. A patient who has received complete information, demonstrated comprehension, and retains decisional capacity has the ethical and legal right to refuse any intervention, even one the clinician believes is in their best interest. The CRNA must respect this decision, document it thoroughly, and provide the best available alternative. Option A violates patient autonomy. Option C is inappropriate; disagreement with a clinician's recommendation is not evidence of psychiatric impairment. Option D constitutes coercion, which invalidates consent.",
